rComments: Shes an amazing professor I honestly enjoyed her so much the first time that I decided to take her again. Shes a great art history professor because shes able to stay on track and doesn't wonder off in her lectures so it makes taking notes really easy and clear to read because its not jumbled up. Shes also approachable and will help you if you ask

Lectures are very long and cover a lot of content. She isnt very exciting to listen to and says just to point out a lot. A lot of stuff tested on is based on lecture. Covers textbook material but only portions. Best to do the posted readings and go to tutorial. Nice prof, approachable but lectures are boring and content heavy.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: One of my favourite art history classes at utm. She is very approachable and gives good feedbacks. Her lectures are engaging and interesting, and you can receive most information for the tests from the lecture.

By far my favourite professor ever. She almost made me switch my major to art history because I loved the subject so much. She's an extremely approachable person. Her passion for her work shows in her teaching. She even said she wished she could have conducted the tutorials for the class I had with her. I'll only take another FAH class with her

She seemed very kind and willing to help, but her lectures didn't really cover anything important. She focused on specific pieces of art and spent half the lecture talking about them, but would then expect students to know a bunch of other works that she never covered or even mentioned. We also fell behind a lot and couldn't even finish the course.

The most sincere and sweetest person I have met! Not only is she passionate about her work, but she wants her students to excel high!  Great lecturer, always helpful, and actually listens to her students. Amazing art history Professor at UTM! Wish more were like her, love her!
She's very passionate about her work and it shows in her lectures. Great professor!

She is very nice and a great lecturer! Make sure you pay attention in lectures becuase she introduces new material that is not in the textbook which is quite helpful! She encourages you to share your opinionswhether they be good or bad in your essays unlike others that just want you to have theirs! Loved this course!

Good Lecturer, well informed, but sometimes as she's explaining her voice disappears...which leaves you sitting on the desk and trying to predict what it is that she wanted to express... Very Helpful, greets your questions with a smile, not the regular "Oh no ! not again, now, what do you want" look, others might have.
